# Nemesis v2 — environment template
# Copy to .env and fill in values:  cp .env.example .env
# NOTHING in this file is a secret. .env itself is gitignored; .env.example is tracked.
# Every variable below is OPTIONAL — the code has sane defaults for all of them.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Paths
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Absolute path to the brain workspace (holds brain.db, features/, repos/, lance/).
# Default: <repo>/workspace  (resolved by brain/config.py)
# Override to relocate the Living Index off-repo, or point tests at a scratch dir
# e.g. BRAIN_WORKSPACE=/tmp/nm-test python -m brain init
# BRAIN_WORKSPACE=

# Absolute path to the repo root. Default: ~/Projects/Agents/nemesis_v2
# Only set this if you cloned to a non-default location AND a script complains.
# NEMESIS_V2_ROOT=

# Where scripts write logs. Default: ~/.nemesis_v2/logs
# NEMESIS_LOG_DIR=

# Scratch dir for transient files (coverage profiles, go-test json). Default: /tmp
# NEMESIS_TMP_DIR=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional integrations (skills degrade gracefully when unset)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Redash REST API key — enables /db-validator payment-SQL formula validation.
# Get it from: https://redash.razorpay.com/profile  (NOT required for core brain/nemesis)
# Leave blank to skip the Redash validation layer.
# REDASH_API_KEY=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NOT environment variables — connect these via Claude Code, never via .env:
#   Slack, Google Drive/Workspace, Gmail, Calendar, Canva  (OAuth MCPs)
# Run ./setup.sh  (or  /nemesis doctor )  to see which MCPs need connecting.
# Tokens are managed by Claude Code's OAuth flow and are NEVER stored in this repo.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
